**1. Port number (line 18)** — High priority
```javascript
app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```
The port `3000` is hardcoded in two places. This should be configurable via `process.env.PORT` so the app can bind to whatever port the hosting environment requires (Heroku, Docker, etc.).

**Suggested fix:**
```javascript
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

